race.comment: WINNY BEE (2) impressed when successful on debut over 950m at Moree 18 months ago and has not been produced since. Has been readied with three strong hitouts in readiness; scoring in all. Looks a promising type that can return with a bang - despite the long break between. On the other hand, TAKING OMAHA (3) definitely doesn't lack fitness and got things back on track last start at Murray Bridge when chasing gamely into a midfield placing in a bunched finished. Boasts peaks that measure up strongly for this and it would be no shock to see him make a return to the winner's circle. STARNOVA (1) will find this a little easier than his last run just eight days ago at Morphettville Parks. Peak fitness now and gets an important 2kg claim. In the mix. RICH LADY (6) has been freshened with 32 days, keeping the legs ticking over with a Murray Bridge trial. Toeroek's booking adds plenty of confidence.
